Turkcell Iletisim Hizmetleri AS (TCELL) ,
Turkeyâ€™s biggest mobile-phone operator, recorded its biggest
gain this year after its first-quarter profit climbed 56
percent, beating estimates.  Turkcell advanced 3.9 percent to 8.98 liras at the close in
Istanbul, the strongest jump since Dec. 20.  Net income rose to 514.8 million liras ($292 million) from
330.1 million liras a year earlier, Turkcell said in a statement
to the  Istanbul Stock Exchange  after the close yesterday. The
year-earlier period included a charge related to its Ukraine
unit.  Turkcell was expected to report a profit of 408.4 million
liras, according to the average of 14 analyst estimates compiled
by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
